voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/9/97/VO_AT_038_DEATH_04.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_038_DEATH_04.wav <death sound>

THE AMAZING RENO.name: The Amazing Reno
THE AMAZING RENO.flavorText: "Reno!" "Please address me by my proper title." " Amazing Reno..."

SATYR OVERSEER.name: Satyr Overseer
SATYR OVERSEER.flavorText: What he lacks in communication skills, he makes up for with highly responsive staffing allocations.

OUTRIDER'S AXE.name: Outrider's Axe
OUTRIDER'S AXE.flavorText: "I only have to get 4 Zhevra hooves? How hard could that be?"

COUNTESS ASHMORE.name: Countess Ashmore
COUNTESS ASHMORE.flavorText: "1 minion… ah, ah, ah! 2 minions… ah, ah, ah! 3 minions… ah, ah, ah!"

CAPTURED JORMUNGAR.name: Captured Jormungar
CAPTURED JORMUNGAR.flavorText: You can keep him, but you have to promise to feed him and clean out his tank every day!

DEMONIC ASSAULT.name: Demonic Assault
DEMONIC ASSAULT.flavorText: Right next to the demonic pepper.

CITY TAX.name: City Tax
CITY TAX.flavorText: "Look pal, I don't care what kind of legion you saved the world from, pay up or else."

SHERIFF BARRELBRIM.name: Sheriff Barrelbrim
SHERIFF BARRELBRIM.flavorText: Is that Sheriff Barrelbrim, owner of the Badlands Barrelbuilding?

SMALL-TIME BUCCANEER.name: Small-Time Buccaneer
SMALL-TIME BUCCANEER.flavorText: "Oh, I'm not serious about it. I only pirate on the weekends."

ALDRACHI WARBLADES.name: Aldrachi Warblades
ALDRACHI WARBLADES.flavorText: The ancient Aldrachi were the greatest warriors in the universe. Imagine their power if they'd put the handle at the END of the blade.

PRIZE VENDOR.name: Prize Vendor
PRIZE VENDOR.flavorText: He's just making sure they're real. Authentic tickets taste like strawberry.

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/b/b8/VO_AT_087_PLAY_ALT1_02.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_087_PLAY_ALT1_02.wav
voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/8/8b/VO_AT_087_ATTACK_04.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_087_ATTACK_04.wav Giddy up!
voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/0/09/VO_AT_087_DEATH_06.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_087_DEATH_06.wav Neigh!

ASTROBIOLOGIST.name: Astrobiologist
ASTROBIOLOGIST.flavorText: Biologists spend a semester abroad. Astrobiologists spend a semester aboard.

TOTEMIC REFLECTION.name: Totemic Reflection
TOTEMIC REFLECTION.flavorText: "Upon reflection, I have decided that your board needs more ME."

CROOKED COOK.name: Crooked Cook
CROOKED COOK.flavorText: There are many things not called poison which can kill a man. But in this case, it is poison.

X-21 REPAIRBOT.name: X-21 Repairbot
X-21 REPAIRBOT.flavorText: The circle bolt goes in the square hole.

LESSER PEARL SPELLSTONE.name: Lesser Pearl Spellstone
LESSER PEARL SPELLSTONE.flavorText: In ages old, when Ancients broke Azari of the Legion spoke To tempt the mortals: gems of power The weak succumbed, their souls devoured.

CONCIERGE.name: Concierge
CONCIERGE.flavorText: So THAT'S who's making all those keys for my Arena runs.

PANDAREN IMPORTER.name: Pandaren Importer
PANDAREN IMPORTER.flavorText: She carries everything you didn't want and more!

MINDBENDER.name: Mindbender
MINDBENDER.flavorText: I like my brain unbent, thanks.

DARING DRAKE.name: Daring Drake
DARING DRAKE.flavorText: First of all, how dare you? Second of all, how dare you!

COMMAND THE ELEMENTS.name: Command the Elements
COMMAND THE ELEMENTS.flavorText: What, you expected a shaman to have trouble with a place called STORMWIND?

GALACTIC CRUSADER.name: Galactic Crusader
GALACTIC CRUSADER.flavorText: The will was very specific that in the event of the Crusader's death, you were to inherit these random spells. Very odd.

JUNGLE JAMMER.name: Jungle Jammer
JUNGLE JAMMER.flavorText: When asked what animal they would be, people always say things like "I'd be wolf-lion hybrid mix. King of the jungle, but still sociable and ferocious." No, you'd be a rat.

SHADOW STRIKE.name: Shadow Strike
SHADOW STRIKE.flavorText: It's like a backstab, only from the front. And with two more stabs.

HERALD VOLAZJ.name: Herald Volazj
HERALD VOLAZJ.flavorText: His whole job is yelling "Yogg-Saron comin'!"

VILEBROOD SKITTERER.name: Vilebrood Skitterer
VILEBROOD SKITTERER.flavorText: It aspires to be a Vilebrood Dancer, but it has eight left feet.

FLAME LEVIATHAN.name: Flame Leviathan
FLAME LEVIATHAN.flavorText: Mimiron likes to take the Flame Leviathan out on some sweet joyrides.

VENGEFUL WALLOPER.name: Vengeful Walloper
VENGEFUL WALLOPER.flavorText: If you can't beat 'em, beat WITH 'em!

BLAZING TRANSMUTATION.name: Blazing Transmutation
BLAZING TRANSMUTATION.flavorText: Congratulations! Your minion evolved into a Fire type!

BEASTMASTER LEOROXX.name: Beastmaster Leoroxx
BEASTMASTER LEOROXX.flavorText: Father of Rexxar, Champion of the Horde, and Flexxar, Champion of the Gym.

RAM TAMER.name: Ram Tamer
RAM TAMER.flavorText: Pump up the ram, pump it up. While your hooves are stompin’.

RAMBUNCTIOUS STUFFY.name: Rambunctious Stuffy
RAMBUNCTIOUS STUFFY.flavorText: The Lich King can't sleep without his stuffy.

FACELESS SUMMONER.name: Faceless Summoner
FACELESS SUMMONER.flavorText: They never get the recognition they deserve.

FEAT OF STRENGTH.name: Feat of Strength
FEAT OF STRENGTH.flavorText: Generally happens right after the airing of grievances.

IMPBALMING.name: Impbalming
IMPBALMING.flavorText: With your complexion, Imp Balm is a great demonizer.

CRAZED WORSHIPPER.name: Crazed Worshipper
CRAZED WORSHIPPER.flavorText: Every month they share a pancake breakfast with the Perfectly Rational Worshippers.

KODO MOUNT.name: Kodo Mount
KODO MOUNT.flavorText: No matter how big they are or how many times you tell them no, they STILL won't stay off the couch.

ROCKET HOPPER.name: Rocket Hopper
ROCKET HOPPER.flavorText: Are y'all gonna ask for THIS one to be orange too!?

WICKED WHISPERS.name: Wicked Whispers
WICKED WHISPERS.flavorText: When the Old Ones whisper, others will scream.

TAR LURKER.name: Tar Lurker
TAR LURKER.flavorText: Hi, Tar here. Long time lurking, first time taunting…

SUPREME ARCHAEOLOGY.name: Supreme Archaeology
SUPREME ARCHAEOLOGY.flavorText: Archaeology is the discovery of rare and powerful artifacts. Supreme Archaeology is TAKING THEM!

POPSICOOLER.name: Popsicooler
POPSICOOLER.flavorText: Just passing through Alterac on its way to apply for a job at the Ice Cream Citadel.

BEARON GLA'SHEAR.name: Bearon Gla'shear
BEARON GLA'SHEAR.flavorText: When you get hit by a royally bad pun, you just have to grin and bear it.

WYRMGUARD.name: Wyrmguard
WYRMGUARD.flavorText: They think they're trusted guardians. Dragons think they're convenient snacks.

MISMATCHED FOSSILS.name: Mismatched Fossils
MISMATCHED FOSSILS.flavorText: Whoever put these fossils together must be really careless.

NETHER BREATH.name: Nether Breath
NETHER BREATH.flavorText: "Whether the Nether is cold, whether the Nether is hot, we'll burn together, whatever the Nether, whether we like it or not."

SWORDFISH.name: Swordfish
SWORDFISH.flavorText: While you were partying, I studied the fish.

LIGHTFUSED STEGODON.name: Lightfused Stegodon
LIGHTFUSED STEGODON.flavorText: “Come now, Johnston. I think those horns are quite fetching on you.”

FREE SPIRIT.name: Free Spirit
FREE SPIRIT.flavorText: His soul was supposed to go to Ardenweald, but you can't chain a free spirit down.

GHOSTLY CHARGER.name: Ghostly Charger
GHOSTLY CHARGER.flavorText: Maybe we should have called him Ghostly Rusher.

AUCTIONMASTER BEARDO.name: Auctionmaster Beardo
AUCTIONMASTER BEARDO.flavorText: Gadgetzan has always run an under-the-table auction house, and business has been PRETTY good for Beardo since the population explosion. And since the explosion that destroyed the competing auction houses in the city.

SOUL REND.name: Soul Rend
SOUL REND.flavorText: About as close to feeling guilt as a warlock's ever going to get.

Y'SHAARJ, THE DEFILER.name: Y'Shaarj, the Defiler
Y'SHAARJ, THE DEFILER.flavorText: Y'Shaarj made an excellent office intern, doing the copying AND defiling.

BLOODWORM.name: Bloodworm
BLOODWORM.flavorText: Queen Lana'thel insists on one of these, fried, every morning for breakfast.

DARING FIRE-EATER.name: Daring Fire-Eater
DARING FIRE-EATER.flavorText: A few hours later he DESTROYED the arena bathrooms.

SUFFOCATE.name: Suffocate
SUFFOCATE.flavorText: He's already floating in the void of space. The shadow magic seems like overkill, idk.

ETHEREAL CONJURER.name: Ethereal Conjurer
ETHEREAL CONJURER.flavorText: Despite the name, he's a solid conjurer.

SKERAM CULTIST.name: Skeram Cultist
SKERAM CULTIST.flavorText: Just before he comes into play, there is an AWESOME training montage with C'Thun.

FEL ORC SOULFIEND.name: Fel Orc Soulfiend
FEL ORC SOULFIEND.flavorText: "Doc says the persistent burning sensation in my soul is probably just an ulcer."

MISTRESS OF MIXTURES.name: Mistress of Mixtures
MISTRESS OF MIXTURES.flavorText: Her favorite mixture is cola and lime.

MAGIC CARPET.name: Magic Carpet
MAGIC CARPET.flavorText: Its small yet fierce riders are affectionately known as rug rats.

VAL'ANYR.name: Val'anyr
VAL'ANYR.flavorText: Recently unearthed in one of the deepest kobold caves. Traded for a large candle.

PIRANHA SWARMER.name: Piranha Swarmer
PIRANHA SWARMER.flavorText: One Fish, Two Fish. Less Fish? You wish.

TRUSTY FISHING ROD.name: Trusty Fishing Rod
TRUSTY FISHING ROD.flavorText: That's weird… I can only catch magic carps with this old fishing rod.

KANGOR, DANCING KING.name: Kangor, Dancing King
KANGOR, DANCING KING.flavorText: After Dr. Boom's involvement with the League of EVIL, Kangor cut ties with the Boomsday Labs and began pursuing his true passion - DISCO!!!

SOUL SHEAR.name: Soul Shear
SOUL SHEAR.flavorText: "Just a little off the sides please."

NATURE STUDIES.name: Nature Studies
NATURE STUDIES.flavorText: "I have a first edition! Go ahead, count the rings."

WALKING FOUNTAIN.name: Walking Fountain
WALKING FOUNTAIN.flavorText: The weirdest part is that it doesn't have legs.

LUCENTBARK.name: Lucentbark
LUCENTBARK.flavorText: Always feels refreshed after a little dirt nap.

voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/7/75/VO_DAL_357_Male_Ancient_Trigger-Resurrected_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_DAL_357_Male_Ancient_Trigger-Resurrected_01.wav Nature calls.

KEENING BANSHEE.name: Keening Banshee
KEENING BANSHEE.flavorText: "What are your strengths?" the interviewer asked. "Well," she replied, "I'm really good at keening."

BENEVOLENT BANKER.name: Benevolent Banker
BENEVOLENT BANKER.flavorText: "Oh no, you've got me confused. I'm Ben, the evil ent banker. I only work with evil trees!"

TARGET DUMMY.name: Target Dummy
TARGET DUMMY.flavorText: The engineering equivalent of a "Kick Me" sticker.

SCRAPSMITH.name: Scrapsmith
SCRAPSMITH.flavorText: Takes the ugly scraps of armor from dead players and combines them into ridiculous looking PVP armor sets.

BAITED ARROW.name: Baited Arrow
BAITED ARROW.flavorText: The card is common, but the steak is rare.

ZUL'DRAK RITUALIST.name: Zul'Drak Ritualist
ZUL'DRAK RITUALIST.flavorText: Generosity is a core value in cult culture.

SPELLZERKER.name: Spellzerker
SPELLZERKER.flavorText: But don’t ask her to use it in a sentence.

FROSTWOLF GRUNT.name: Frostwolf Grunt
FROSTWOLF GRUNT.flavorText: Grunting is what his father did and his father before that. It's more than just a job.

SCRAPBOOKING STUDENT.name: Scrapbooking Student
SCRAPBOOKING STUDENT.flavorText: "…and this is the time I rode a dinosaur, and this is the time that I helped solve a murder, and this is the time I got corrupted by the Old Gods..."

LEECHING POISON.name: Leeching Poison
LEECHING POISON.flavorText: No actual leeches were harmed in the creation of this card.

KING PLUSH.name: King Plush
KING PLUSH.flavorText: He's so fluffy you're gonna DIE!

SUNSTRUCK HENCHMAN.name: Sunstruck Henchman
SUNSTRUCK HENCHMAN.flavorText: There is E.V.I.L. here that DOES sleep.

ORION, MANSION MANAGER.name: Orion, Mansion Manager
ORION, MANSION MANAGER.flavorText: The secrets of the universe are vast... and will be revealed sometime later this game.

SHELLSHIFTER.name: Shellshifter
SHELLSHIFTER.flavorText: Master of the Three Shell Monte.

BRASS ELEMENTAL.name: Brass Elemental
BRASS ELEMENTAL.flavorText: You handle the water spells. It's got the earth, wind, and fire covered.

TRUESILVER CHAMPION.name: Truesilver Champion
TRUESILVER CHAMPION.flavorText: It Slices, it Dices. You can cut a tin can with it. (But you wouldn't want to.)

ELITIST SNOB.name: Elitist Snob
ELITIST SNOB.flavorText: "I heard the Sire invited a Murloc! How dreadful!"

REVENGE OF THE WILD.name: Revenge of the Wild
REVENGE OF THE WILD.flavorText: My roommates only use Revenge of the Passive Aggressive.

REBUKE.name: Rebuke
REBUKE.flavorText: When one buke just isn’t enough.

DUSKFALLEN AVIANA.name: Duskfallen Aviana
DUSKFALLEN AVIANA.flavorText: Someone called her "Tweety". She didn't take it well.

CRUSHING HAND.name: Crushing Hand
CRUSHING HAND.flavorText: Shamans always have the firmest handshakes.

PROFESSOR PUTRICIDE.name: Professor Putricide
PROFESSOR PUTRICIDE.flavorText: Among his more notable inventions: A tentacle-groomer, a plague that would wipe out all life on Azeroth, and a fidget spinner.

STONESKIN BASILISK.name: Stoneskin Basilisk
STONESKIN BASILISK.flavorText: He got that way from looking into a mirror.

GRIMESTREET INFORMANT.name: Grimestreet Informant
GRIMESTREET INFORMANT.flavorText: "Naw, naw. You're talkin' about Grime BOULEVARD. I ain't know nuthin' 'bout that."

SOULBOUND ASHTONGUE.name: Soulbound Ashtongue
SOULBOUND ASHTONGUE.flavorText: He claims to be "soulbound," but I just think he's clingy.

THIRSTY DRIFTER.name: Thirsty Drifter
THIRSTY DRIFTER.flavorText: Quick! Someone bring her a Manathirst card!

SAVAGE COMBATANT.name: Savage Combatant
SAVAGE COMBATANT.flavorText: Maybe if you whistle a tune it will soothe him. Yeah... Try that.

ARCANE QUIVER.name: Arcane Quiver
ARCANE QUIVER.flavorText: "Quiver in fear!" - The Lich King "Ok." - Me

CEREMONIAL MAUL.name: Ceremonial Maul
CEREMONIAL MAUL.flavorText: For the most discerning of hall monitors.

GRIMESTREET PROTECTOR.name: Grimestreet Protector
GRIMESTREET PROTECTOR.flavorText: Some new asphalt should do the trick.

CONTAMINATED LASHER.name: Contaminated Lasher
CONTAMINATED LASHER.flavorText: He corrupts me, he corrupts me not.

WILD SPIRITS.name: Wild Spirits
WILD SPIRITS.flavorText: Wait, this card just released! It should be Standard Spirits!

SHIMMERING SUNFISH.name: Shimmering Sunfish
SHIMMERING SUNFISH.flavorText: Just keep shimmering, just keep shimmering.

VIOLET HAZE.name: Violet Haze
VIOLET HAZE.flavorText: Elite Tauren Chieftain's next hit single.

KOBOLD LIBRARIAN.name: Kobold Librarian
KOBOLD LIBRARIAN.flavorText: Kobolds sort books using a gooey decimal system.

AUCTIONHOUSE GAVEL.name: Auctionhouse Gavel
AUCTIONHOUSE GAVEL.flavorText: "I want to be a judge! Or an auctioneer! Look, all I want is one of those sweet, tiny hammers."

TRAVEL AGENT.name: Travel Agent
TRAVEL AGENT.flavorText: I could've hired her or some Dodo.

CANDLERAISER.name: Candleraiser
CANDLERAISER.flavorText: You would not believe your eyes If ten million kobold guys Lit up the world to this ogre beat

FIRE PLUME PHOENIX.name: Fire Plume Phoenix
FIRE PLUME PHOENIX.flavorText: This is what happens when you use a volcano as a bird bath.

LIGHTFORGED CARIEL.name: Lightforged Cariel
LIGHTFORGED CARIEL.flavorText: Her faith, unshakable. Her shield, immovable. Her enemies, irredeemable.

DISPOSE OF EVIDENCE.name: Dispose of Evidence
DISPOSE OF EVIDENCE.flavorText: Just because you did it doesn't mean you have to be guilty.

EXARCH HATAARU.name: Exarch Hataaru
EXARCH HATAARU.flavorText: Severely outmatched by the Burning Legion, the Draenei had no hopes of survival… That changed with the invention of arkonite crystals, giving Hataaru and his Artificers new ways to empower their people.

TONY, KING OF PIRACY.name: Tony, King of Piracy
TONY, KING OF PIRACY.flavorText: Tony prefers sailing on torrents rather than streams.

TWILIGHT TORRENT.name: Twilight Torrent
TWILIGHT TORRENT.flavorText: I hope it’s the first one.

THE BOOGEYMONSTER.name: The Boogeymonster
THE BOOGEYMONSTER.flavorText: Has 20 years of training in classical ballet, but ALLLLLL he ever gets asked to do is boogie.

BLESSED GOODS.name: Blessed Goods
BLESSED GOODS.flavorText: Guaranteed to contain no haunted dolls, cursed rings, or corrupted runeblades, or your money back.

TWILIGHT ACOLYTE.name: Twilight Acolyte
TWILIGHT ACOLYTE.flavorText: The dragons mostly keep him around as a snack.

FURIOUS FELFIN.name: Furious Felfin
FURIOUS FELFIN.flavorText: Signature moves include Eye Bream, Feast of Soles, and Metamorphofish.

BOOGIE DOWN.name: Boogie Down
BOOGIE DOWN.flavorText: Whatever you do, do NOT sashay to the right.

ASHTONGUE SLAYER.name: Ashtongue Slayer
ASHTONGUE SLAYER.flavorText: Her other hand attachments include a corkscrew and a bottle opener.

NELLIE, THE GREAT THRESHER.name: Nellie, the Great Thresher
NELLIE, THE GREAT THRESHER.flavorText: Not to be mistaken for her freshwater cousin, Nessie, this massive creature was harnessed to carry Hooktusk's favorite ship.

STEWARD OF SCROLLS.name: Steward of Scrolls
STEWARD OF SCROLLS.flavorText: Oh dang it, I spilled ink elemental all over my essay!

TENTACLE GRIP.name: Tentacle Grip
TENTACLE GRIP.flavorText: "WINTER VEIL WAS MONTHS AGO, WHY ARE YOUR LIGHTS STILL UP?"

DUSKBAT.name: Duskbat
DUSKBAT.flavorText: Happily married with two kids. It was love at first bite.

GARROTE.name: Garrote
GARROTE.flavorText: "I don't have money… but what I do have is a particular set of skills."

WORTHY EXPEDITION.name: Worthy Expedition
WORTHY EXPEDITION.flavorText: This isn't where I parked my mount.

CORAL KEEPER.name: Coral Keeper
CORAL KEEPER.flavorText: This here is Carl. They're in charge of these elementals. Not all of them get along, so sometimes Carl corrals the quarreling coral.

SQUIRMING TENTACLE.name: Squirming Tentacle
SQUIRMING TENTACLE.flavorText: Yeah, I think we can agree that killing the squirming tentacle first is a good idea.

PUFFERFIST.name: Pufferfist
PUFFERFIST.flavorText: "...and then I'll hit 'em with the ol' puffercut!"

DOZING DRAGON.name: Dozing Dragon
DOZING DRAGON.flavorText: Emerald dreams can become emerald realities.

DON'T STAND IN THE FIRE!.name: Don't Stand in the Fire!
DON'T STAND IN THE FIRE!.flavorText: Apparently the “Caution: Hot Surface” sign had burned up.

VELEN'S CHOSEN.name: Velen's Chosen
VELEN'S CHOSEN.flavorText: Velen wrote a "Lovely Card" for Tyrande with a picture of the Deeprun Tram that said "I Choo-Choo-Choose you!"

HOLOMANCER.name: Holomancer
HOLOMANCER.flavorText: Help me, worthy opponent. You're my only hope.

TWIN TYRANT.name: Twin Tyrant
TWIN TYRANT.flavorText: They can never agree on whether it's too hot or too cold.

OZRUK.name: Ozruk
OZRUK.flavorText: Between you and me, Ozruk is a bit obsessed with his body.

DUSKBREAKER.name: Duskbreaker
DUSKBREAKER.flavorText: Waking up at the break of dusk is just not as impressive.

SHADOW OF DEMISE.name: Shadow of Demise
SHADOW OF DEMISE.flavorText: Each time you cast a spell, transform this into a copy of its flavor text.

DEATH'S HEAD CULTIST.name: Death's Head Cultist
DEATH'S HEAD CULTIST.flavorText: Nothing can stop death. Except a Taunt. With Healing.

GIFT OF THE WILD.name: Gift of the Wild
GIFT OF THE WILD.flavorText: The gift that keeps on living.

DARK PEDDLER.name: Dark Peddler
DARK PEDDLER.flavorText: I'm offering you a bargain here! This amazing vacuum cleaner for your soul!

WRATHSCALE NAGA.name: Wrathscale Naga
WRATHSCALE NAGA.flavorText: If throwing glaives is what you crave; summon tokens and make 'em broken.

CONVINCING INFILTRATOR.name: Convincing Infiltrator
CONVINCING INFILTRATOR.flavorText: It’s always nice to steal a familiar face.

SHADEHOUND.name: Shadehound
SHADEHOUND.flavorText: This Shadehound wasn't just a good boy. He was the best.

ARCHIVIST ELYSIANA.name: Archivist Elysiana
ARCHIVIST ELYSIANA.flavorText: Your deck is just another organizational challenge to her.

SKYFIN.name: Skyfin
SKYFIN.flavorText: "Do you want to be a murloc or a dragon?" "Yes."

N'ZOTH'S FIRST MATE.name: N'Zoth's First Mate
N'ZOTH'S FIRST MATE.flavorText: Hates when N'Zoth yells "Ahoy Matey!!", but there's not really much he can do about it.

PILOTED SKY GOLEM.name: Piloted Sky Golem
PILOTED SKY GOLEM.flavorText: The pinnacle of goblin engineering. Includes an espresso machine and foot massager.

KVALDIR RAIDER.name: Kvaldir Raider
KVALDIR RAIDER.flavorText: Coming soon... to a tuskarr village near you!

TURALYON, THE TENURED.name: Turalyon, the Tenured
TURALYON, THE TENURED.flavorText: "Let evil flee before righteousness; let the innocent live in peace. Let the day come when none need fear. For that day, I give my life gladly."

THE CAVERNS BELOW.name: The Caverns Below
THE CAVERNS BELOW.flavorText: Why can't it ever be The Taverns Below?

THE DARK PORTAL.name: The Dark Portal
THE DARK PORTAL.flavorText: Some say it's the source of Azeroth's greatest problems—aside from the gnomes.

DRAGONRIDER TALRITHA.name: Dragonrider Talritha
DRAGONRIDER TALRITHA.flavorText: You can't just run away from your problems. Unless you have another dragon to jump to.

JAM SESSION.name: Jam Session
JAM SESSION.flavorText: Their skills will make you jelly.

SYMPHONY OF SINS.name: Symphony of Sins
SYMPHONY OF SINS.flavorText: Makes for some killer final boss music.

BONEDIGGER GEIST.name: Bonedigger Geist
BONEDIGGER GEIST.flavorText: He's a grave-half-full kind of geist.

IMPRISONED FELMAW.name: Imprisoned Felmaw
IMPRISONED FELMAW.flavorText: It doesn't care who woke it up, someone's getting bitten.

RIN, ORCHESTRATOR OF DOOM.name: Rin, Orchestrator of Doom
RIN, ORCHESTRATOR OF DOOM.flavorText: Rin's orchestra is the best of the best. When your replacement is just one summoning away, you have to play perfectly.

SERPENT EGG.name: Serpent Egg
SERPENT EGG.flavorText: These things go from "adorable danger noodle!" to "MY FACE IS MELTING!" all too quickly.

ALARMED SECURITYBOT.name: Alarmed Securitybot
ALARMED SECURITYBOT.flavorText: THREAT LEVEL: 5! Which doesn't actually sound that bad to be honest.

NEFERSET RITUALIST.name: Neferset Ritualist
NEFERSET RITUALIST.flavorText: The Neferset are great—they'll always make sure their friends are feline fine.

FELFIRE DEADEYE.name: Felfire Deadeye
FELFIRE DEADEYE.flavorText: She only shoots people who pet her cat without asking first.

NARAIN SOOTHFANCY.name: Narain Soothfancy
NARAIN SOOTHFANCY.flavorText: I predict... that you will be very happy with your reading!

DISPATCH KODO.name: Dispatch Kodo
DISPATCH KODO.flavorText: "Crime reported at First Bank of Gadgetzan. Huge quantities of Jade being carried away by what looks like a bunch of Hozen. Kodo 77 can you make it over there now?"

FRIENDLY BARTENDER.name: Friendly Bartender
FRIENDLY BARTENDER.flavorText: "What'll it be? A Jade Brew? A Grimy Goose? A Kabal Manatini?"

GREEDY PARTNER.name: Greedy Partner
GREEDY PARTNER.flavorText: "Don't worry, we'll evenly split the bounty. Then I'll have two evenly sized piles of gold!"

MINDRENDER ILLUCIA.name: Mindrender Illucia
MINDRENDER ILLUCIA.flavorText: "…and that's how I ended up with a Murloc Cultural Studies major."

GRIFTAH, TRUSTED VENDOR.name: Griftah, Trusted Vendor
GRIFTAH, TRUSTED VENDOR.flavorText: "Tiki mugs will match any kind of home décor! They're timeless!"

LIGHT'S CHAMPION.name: Light's Champion
LIGHT'S CHAMPION.flavorText: When there's something strange (say, a gibbering demon) in your neighborhood, who are you going to call?

CINDERSTORM.name: Cinderstorm
CINDERSTORM.flavorText: Forecast: "Cloudy with a chance of fireballs."

CORRUPTION.name: Corruption
CORRUPTION.flavorText: It starts with stealing a pen from work, and before you know it, BOOOM! Corrupted!

BLADEMASTER OKANI.name: Blademaster Okani
BLADEMASTER OKANI.flavorText: Yet ANOTHER sword fighter that spams counters.

JIVE, INSECT!.name: JIVE, INSECT!
JIVE, INSECT!.flavorText: "WHY IS NO ONE JIVING? I SPECIFICALLY REQUESTED IT!"

ARCANE WYRM.name: Arcane Wyrm
ARCANE WYRM.flavorText: Arcane Bolt on you, Arcane Bolt on your cow, Arcane Bolt on your whole family!

STARFIRE.name: Starfire
STARFIRE.flavorText: Balance is important to druids. This card is perfectly balanced.

SQUASHLING.name: Squashling
SQUASHLING.flavorText: Everyone hail to the squashling song!

UPGRADED REPAIR BOT.name: Upgraded Repair Bot
UPGRADED REPAIR BOT.flavorText: It's the same as the previous generation but they slapped the word "upgraded" on it to sell it for double.

SATHROVARR.name: Sathrovarr
SATHROVARR.flavorText: Just wait until you also find a copy in your pocket. And your desk! And your FRIDGE!!

BOOTY BAY BODYGUARD.name: Booty Bay Bodyguard
BOOTY BAY BODYGUARD.flavorText: You can hire him... until someone offers him enough gold to turn on you.

FESTIVAL SECURITY.name: Festival Security
FESTIVAL SECURITY.flavorText: "Incident in the mosh pit? Copy that, be there in a year."

CLIMBING HOOK.name: Climbing Hook
CLIMBING HOOK.flavorText: "It LOOKS like a grappling hook but it's actually a climbing hook. It's a really important distinction you just wouldn't get it."

SERRATED BONE SPIKE.name: Serrated Bone Spike
SERRATED BONE SPIKE.flavorText: Draka, in an attempt to help, threw them a bone.

FREYA, KEEPER OF NATURE.name: Freya, Keeper of Nature
FREYA, KEEPER OF NATURE.flavorText: Good things come in pairs. Good things come in pairs.

RANGARI SCOUT.name: Rangari Scout
RANGARI SCOUT.flavorText: Always takes credit for other people's discoveries.

RAPTOR HATCHLING.name: Raptor Hatchling
RAPTOR HATCHLING.flavorText: They’re just baby teeth. Lots and lots of baby teeth.

WOODCUTTER'S AXE.name: Woodcutter's Axe
WOODCUTTER'S AXE.flavorText: It's a lumberjack's axe and that's ok.

GREATER ARCANE MISSILES.name: Greater Arcane Missiles
GREATER ARCANE MISSILES.flavorText: Wow, and I thought Arcane Missiles was great!

VOLCANOSAUR.name: Volcanosaur
VOLCANOSAUR.flavorText: Always fun to say out loud "VOL-CA-NO-SAUUUR!"

LANCE CARRIER.name: Lance Carrier
LANCE CARRIER.flavorText: Lance Carrier is an obscure entry level position in orcish armies. A mystery, since orcs don't generally use lances.

PERDITION'S BLADE.name: Perdition's Blade
PERDITION'S BLADE.flavorText: Perdition's Blade is Ragnaros's back-up weapon while Sulfuras is in the shop.

PRINCESS HUHURAN.name: Princess Huhuran
PRINCESS HUHURAN.flavorText: She flitters around Ahn'Qiraj dreaming of the day she will meet a sweet prince, whom she can lay thousands of eggs with.

TOMB PILLAGER.name: Tomb Pillager
TOMB PILLAGER.flavorText: After the guild broke up, he could no longer raid the tombs.

AXE BERSERKER.name: Axe Berserker
AXE BERSERKER.flavorText: All the body spray went to her head.

SPLITTING AXE.name: Splitting Axe
SPLITTING AXE.flavorText: The ancient shaman chant, "Control Axe, Control Vee."

TUNNEL TROGG.name: Tunnel Trogg
TUNNEL TROGG.flavorText: Sure, they're ugly, but they live in tunnels. You try your beauty routine without natural light.

CORRUPTING MIST.name: Corrupting Mist
CORRUPTING MIST.flavorText: The most terrifying of Un’goro magics is both silent… AND deadly.

LILIAN VOSS.name: Lilian Voss
LILIAN VOSS.flavorText: She doesn't feel pity, or remorse, or fear. And she absolutely will not stop... ever, until all necromancers are dead.

DUST DEVIL.name: Dust Devil
DUST DEVIL.flavorText: Westfall is full of dust devils. And buzzards. And crazed golems. And pirates. Why does anyone live here?

ELEMENTAL DESTRUCTION.name: Elemental Destruction
ELEMENTAL DESTRUCTION.flavorText: I'm not a shaman or anything, but isn't Elemental Destruction the opposite of what they want to do?

BLAZING ACCRETION.name: Blazing Accretion
BLAZING ACCRETION.flavorText: Much like the Draenei, this Elemental just wants a place to call home. Unlike the Draenei, it incinerates everything it touches.

TUNNEL BLASTER.name: Tunnel Blaster
TUNNEL BLASTER.flavorText: And you always thought they wore the candles just for fun.

LIGHTRAY.name: Lightray
LIGHTRAY.flavorText: Lightrays, much like rays of light, tend to be seen closer to the surface.

SHADOW SENSEI.name: Shadow Sensei
SHADOW SENSEI.flavorText: He used to be Aya's tutor, but she fired him for bugging her too much.

THUNDER BLUFF VALIANT.name: Thunder Bluff Valiant
THUNDER BLUFF VALIANT.flavorText: Allowing totems to attack is not cheating. I mean, there isn't anything in the rule books about it.

HEART OF THE LEGION.name: Heart of the Legion
HEART OF THE LEGION.flavorText: It grew 3 sizes after trying to steal Winter Veil.

FACELESS RAGER.name: Faceless Rager
FACELESS RAGER.flavorText: When you need to rage anonymously.

SUPERNOVA.name: Supernova
SUPERNOVA.flavorText: People who enjoy the heat will say this looks like perfect weather.

LESSER MITHRIL SPELLSTONE.name: Lesser Mithril Spellstone
LESSER MITHRIL SPELLSTONE.flavorText: To dwarves of stone the demon called With promises of might, enthralled In grasping greed they found their doom Forever bound in mithril tombs.

OMEGA AGENT.name: Omega Agent
OMEGA AGENT.flavorText: They don't just find the truth. They give it a ten second head start, then hunt it down.

IRONHIDE DIREHORN.name: Ironhide Direhorn
IRONHIDE DIREHORN.flavorText: "Boy! Bring me my masks and skull rams."

MO'ARG DRILLFIST.name: Mo'arg Drillfist
MO'ARG DRILLFIST.flavorText: Also functions as the town dentist.

CARRESS, CABARET STAR.name: Carress, Cabaret Star
CARRESS, CABARET STAR.flavorText: Some Naga use their mastery over the elements to go on villainous conquests. Others put on a show!

RAZA THE RESEALED.name: Raza the Resealed
RAZA THE RESEALED.flavorText: The 10th anniversary edition of a classic bestseller!

ALL YOU CAN EAT.name: All You Can Eat
ALL YOU CAN EAT.flavorText: Never design cards when you're hungry.

DISGUISED K'THIR.name: Disguised K'thir
DISGUISED K'THIR.flavorText: That is not a very good disguise, dude.

DARK POSSESSION.name: Dark Possession
DARK POSSESSION.flavorText: Wanted on three counts of gnomish possession.

STARSCALE CONSTELLAR.name: Starscale Constellar
STARSCALE CONSTELLAR.flavorText: You'll understand how to best make use of its effect once you connect the dots.

TREACHERY.name: Treachery
TREACHERY.flavorText: Never look a gift minion in the mouth.

N'ZOTH, GOD OF THE DEEP.name: N'Zoth, God of the Deep
N'ZOTH, GOD OF THE DEEP.flavorText: It really just wants to cuddle all the creatures of Azeroth.

BARAK KODOBANE.name: Barak Kodobane
BARAK KODOBANE.flavorText: They say he's a pro at horseback archery.

DEW PROCESS.name: Dew Process
DEW PROCESS.flavorText: All part of dewing your dew diligence.

HOARD PILLAGER.name: Hoard Pillager
HOARD PILLAGER.flavorText: Better to have stabbed and lost. And then found again!

JADE BEHEMOTH.name: Jade Behemoth
JADE BEHEMOTH.flavorText: I think we should talk about the jade elephant in the room.

E.M.P. OPERATIVE.name: E.M.P. Operative
E.M.P. OPERATIVE.flavorText: "I said this looks like a job for me So everybody just follow me 'Cause we need a little E.M.P. 'Cause it feels so mechy without me…"

GORLOC RAVAGER.name: Gorloc Ravager
GORLOC RAVAGER.flavorText: Be careful what you fish for.

GRAVELSNOUT KNIGHT.name: Gravelsnout Knight
GRAVELSNOUT KNIGHT.flavorText: The mole of La Mancha rides again!

REVENGE.name: Revenge
REVENGE.flavorText: This is better than Arcane Explosion, so I guess warriors are finally getting revenge on mages for Mortal Strike being worse than Fireball.

SPELLWEAVER.name: Spellweaver
SPELLWEAVER.flavorText: Spells offer twice the moisture wicking of cotton.

EREDAR DECEPTOR.name: Eredar Deceptor
EREDAR DECEPTOR.flavorText: But they were all of them deceived, for another Eredar was made.

RENO THE RELICOLOGIST.name: Reno the Relicologist
RENO THE RELICOLOGIST.flavorText: All his life, Reno Jackson was only a gatling wand away from becoming the greatest and most terrifying mage who ever existed.

SILVERMOON ARCANIST.name: Silvermoon Arcanist
SILVERMOON ARCANIST.flavorText: This turn only, I'm something of an Arcanist myself.

DARING REPORTER.name: Daring Reporter
DARING REPORTER.flavorText: She's working on a story! While skydiving!

MAGTHERIDON.name: Magtheridon
MAGTHERIDON.flavorText: Came from another world to invade Outland and bend it to his will… only to be overthrown by an elf from another world who invaded Outland and bent it to his will.

DEATH BLOSSOM WHOMPER.name: Death Blossom Whomper
DEATH BLOSSOM WHOMPER.flavorText: We call her Audrey II. She was named after her mother.

ANCESTRAL GUARDIAN.name: Ancestral Guardian
ANCESTRAL GUARDIAN.flavorText: No one knows whose ancestor he is, but he's still upset that you never call.

MEKGINEER THERMAPLUGG.name: Mekgineer Thermaplugg
MEKGINEER THERMAPLUGG.flavorText: He was obsessed with explosives until he discovered knitting. Now he yells, “SWEATERS! MORE SWEATERS!”

STORM CHASER.name: Storm Chaser
STORM CHASER.flavorText: Best drank after a stiff gale.

STALAGG.name: Stalagg
STALAGG.flavorText: Stalagg want to write own flavor text. "STALAGG AWESOME!"

AMAN'THUL.name: Aman'Thul
AMAN'THUL.flavorText: The leader of the titans was the first to awaken. In his loneliness, he sought out other titans across many different worlds, and together, they formed the Pantheon.

EXPLOSIVE TRAP.name: Explosive Trap
EXPLOSIVE TRAP.flavorText: It traps your food AND cooks it for you!

FLY OFF THE SHELVES.name: Fly Off the Shelves
FLY OFF THE SHELVES.flavorText: No, Whizbang, you can't pass off a poorly made shelf as a cool Priest spell.

EVASION.name: Evasion
EVASION.flavorText: Works on weapons, missiles, and taxes.

TABLETOP ROLEPLAYER.name: Tabletop Roleplayer
TABLETOP ROLEPLAYER.flavorText: "And then I uh... I curse them with... uh... OH! I got it! They have to speak in rhymes or they turn into a crab!"

DEATHWEAVER AURA.name: Deathweaver Aura
DEATHWEAVER AURA.flavorText: Knitting is a harmless hobby. Weaving, though...

LOAN SHARK.name: Loan Shark
LOAN SHARK.flavorText: Pay up or you'll be swimming with the fishes.

SAVAGE YMIRJAR.name: Savage Ymirjar
SAVAGE YMIRJAR.flavorText: When is an Undead door not an Undead door? When it's a(Ymir)jar!

FROST ELEMENTAL.name: Frost Elemental
FROST ELEMENTAL.flavorText: When a Water elemental and an Ice elemental love each other VERY much...

LION'S GUARD.name: Lion's Guard
LION'S GUARD.flavorText: She takes the lion's share of the credit, too.

ULTRASAUR.name: Ultrasaur
ULTRASAUR.flavorText: Evolved the really long neck to spy on its neighbors.

REVERBERATIONS.name: Reverberations
REVERBERATIONS.flavorText: This sounds much louder in the void.

STEGODON.name: Stegodon
STEGODON.flavorText: Level 40 Tortollan Paladins quest to tame a Stegodon. There are no level 41 Tortollan Paladins.

HARMONICA SOLOIST.name: Harmonica Soloist
HARMONICA SOLOIST.flavorText: A magician never reveals their Secrets. A musician on the other hand...

EVIL HECKLER.name: Evil Heckler
EVIL HECKLER.flavorText: To be honest, heckling is not the most effective form of evil.

KIRI, CHOSEN OF ELUNE.name: Kiri, Chosen of Elune
KIRI, CHOSEN OF ELUNE.flavorText: Now, when the Sun is between the Moon and the Azeroth... that's when you've got a problem.

COGMASTER.name: Cogmaster
COGMASTER.flavorText: After a while, you don't see the cogs and sprockets. All you see is a robot, a spider tank, a deathray...

POWER WORD: SHIELD.name: Power Word: Shield
POWER WORD: SHIELD.flavorText: Sure the extra protection is nice, but the shield really reduces visibility.

CATACLYSM.name: Cataclysm
CATACLYSM.flavorText: RUN FROM SKY CANDLES! THEY BURN! RUN!

LORD BAROV.name: Lord Barov
LORD BAROV.flavorText: Alexei Barov stayed at Scholomance despite leasing it to Kel’Thuzad. He says it’s for "supervision."

GUFF RUNETOTEM.name: Guff Runetotem
GUFF RUNETOTEM.flavorText: "By the twins above and twins below, our companions will lead us through." —Guff Runetotem

K'THIR RITUALIST.name: K'thir Ritualist
K'THIR RITUALIST.flavorText: Something evil this way comes… and it's bringing friends over!

RECURRING VILLAIN.name: Recurring Villain
RECURRING VILLAIN.flavorText: Mwahahaha! You'll never catch him this time!

PROTECT THE KING!.name: Protect the King!
PROTECT THE KING!.flavorText: Form ranks! Everyone into the King's Tuskarr Defense!

DREAMWAY GUARDIANS.name: Dreamway Guardians
DREAMWAY GUARDIANS.flavorText: They're a nightmare to deal with.

CHILLMAW.name: Chillmaw
CHILLMAW.flavorText: Chillmaw keeps trying to ruin the Grand Tournament, and she would've done it too, if it weren't for those dang kids!

NERUBIAN FLYER.name: Nerubian Flyer
NERUBIAN FLYER.flavorText: Undead Air Miles only cover Northrend and the surrounding coast.

STUBBORN SUSPECT.name: Stubborn Suspect
STUBBORN SUSPECT.flavorText: He keeps saying "I'll never talk," but no one has actually asked him anything.

CHAOTIC CONSUMPTION.name: Chaotic Consumption
CHAOTIC CONSUMPTION.flavorText: You're not you when you're hungry.

PRESTOR'S PYROMANCER.name: Prestor's Pyromancer
PRESTOR'S PYROMANCER.flavorText: Ah, yeah. This guy. Definitely not an evil dragon in disguise either.

MEDDLESOME SERVANT.name: Meddlesome Servant
MEDDLESOME SERVANT.flavorText: Has successfully gotten away with it too.

MANKRIK.name: Mankrik
MANKRIK.flavorText: Relives his nightmare every day a new Horde player is created.

SHUDDERBLOCK.name: Shudderblock
SHUDDERBLOCK.flavorText: Beware the hinges that pinch, the scales that splinter!

KING'S DEFENDER.name: King's Defender
KING'S DEFENDER.flavorText: "King's Attacker" is a shield. Funny, huh?

DEATH BEETLE.name: Death Beetle
DEATH BEETLE.flavorText: Well that'll be useless next expansion. WINK WINK.

TROLLEY PROBLEM.name: Trolley Problem
TROLLEY PROBLEM.flavorText: If only there were thousands of hypotheticals to prepare me for this moment!

HEADMASTER KEL'THUZAD.name: Headmaster Kel'Thuzad
HEADMASTER KEL'THUZAD.flavorText: "You wish to know my secrets, hmm? I carry little bits of tuna in the sleeves of my robe, he loves that. Oh, you meant the risen dead? That was trivial, trivial."

MIRROR IMAGE.name: Mirror Image
MIRROR IMAGE.flavorText: Oh hey it's Mirror Image! !egamI rorriM s'ti yeh hO

TORTOLLAN PRIMALIST.name: Tortollan Primalist
TORTOLLAN PRIMALIST.flavorText: I see pizza in my future.

VINECLEAVER.name: Vinecleaver
VINECLEAVER.flavorText: George and Karl! Thank the Light we found you!

RAID BOSS ONYXIA.name: Raid Boss Onyxia
RAID BOSS ONYXIA.flavorText: Onyxia chose her guises to manipulate mortals, but her true form? That was reserved for ending them.

AZSHARAN TRIDENT.name: Azsharan Trident
AZSHARAN TRIDENT.flavorText: Nevermind the barnacles! A well-crafted weapon is eternally useful.

TIDAL REVENANT.name: Tidal Revenant
TIDAL REVENANT.flavorText: A big minion that clears the board and gains Armor? Wow, Warrior is really in their element now.

REMIXED MUSICIAN.name: Remixed Musician
REMIXED MUSICIAN.flavorText: Like every bard I know, he's a chaotic Neutral jack of all trades.

SI:7 SMUGGLER.name: SI:7 Smuggler
SI:7 SMUGGLER.flavorText: After a while, Onyxia's regurgitated rats start to taste pretty good.

WARDRUID LOTI.name: Wardruid Loti
WARDRUID LOTI.flavorText: “Ravasaur!” “Pretty scary” “…Blammodax!” “Is that a thing?” “SMAXODON!” “….now you’re just making those up.”

ANDUIN'S GIFT.name: Anduin's Gift
ANDUIN'S GIFT.flavorText: "My council assures me this is the perfect gift! Not that they needed to tell me. I know what's in there." -Anduin

XB-931 HOUSEKEEPER.name: XB-931 Housekeeper
XB-931 HOUSEKEEPER.flavorText: "WHAT IS MY PURPOSE?" "You gain Armor." "OH GOD."

WRIGGLING HORROR.name: Wriggling Horror
WRIGGLING HORROR.flavorText: Created to scare. Born to wriggle.

PROSPECTOR'S CARAVAN.name: Prospector's Caravan
PROSPECTOR'S CARAVAN.flavorText: Prospectors came from all around in the Golden Legendary Rush of '49.

HARMONIC METAL.name: Harmonic Metal
HARMONIC METAL.flavorText: I have bashed together plenty of pieces of metal in my day and not ONCE has it sounded harmonic.

TROGG GLOOMEATER.name: Trogg Gloomeater
TROGG GLOOMEATER.flavorText: His breath smells like agony and despair, which is still better than most troggs.

SERPENT WIG.name: Serpent Wig
SERPENT WIG.flavorText: Legends say that all those who look into her eyes are turned to plush.

BLOOD WARRIORS.name: Blood Warriors
BLOOD WARRIORS.flavorText: They have an uneasy rivalry with the Blood Paladins.

VOLLEY MAUL.name: Volley Maul
VOLLEY MAUL.flavorText: "It's all fun and games until someone gets hurt." - LAME PARTY POOPERS

SIGIL OF SUMMONING.name: Sigil of Summoning
SIGIL OF SUMMONING.flavorText: Look, summoning ain’t exactly a science. Sometimes it takes a turn.

KNIGHT OF THE WILD.name: Knight of the Wild
KNIGHT OF THE WILD.flavorText: He gets a discount on the tournament entry fee because he is his own horse.

VILEFIEND TRAINER.name: Vilefiend Trainer
VILEFIEND TRAINER.flavorText: My Vilefiend Trainers give me a much better sprint than my Air Gul'dans.

TORTOLLAN FORAGER.name: Tortollan Forager
TORTOLLAN FORAGER.flavorText: In the Tortollan tongue, Un’goro is known as the “Land of the Lost and Found.”

DOUBLING IMP.name: Doubling Imp
DOUBLING IMP.flavorText: What's worse than finding two imps in your lab? Only finding one of them.

FLAME LANCE.name: Flame Lance
FLAME LANCE.flavorText: It's on the rack next to ice lance, acid lance, and English muffin lance.

FEAST AND FAMINE.name: Feast and Famine
FEAST AND FAMINE.flavorText: Please sir, may I have some armor?

ARMAGEDILLO.name: Armagedillo
ARMAGEDILLO.flavorText: We may never know what provoked it, but we will never forget the consequences.

ONE-EYED CHEAT.name: One-eyed Cheat
ONE-EYED CHEAT.flavorText: When pirates say there is no "Eye" in "team," they are very literal about it.

XOR'TOTH, BREAKER OF STARS.name: Xor'toth, Breaker of Stars
XOR'TOTH, BREAKER OF STARS.flavorText: We started his stats at 50,000,000,000/50,000,000,000 to be lore-accurate, but it was just a nudge too powerful.

BESTIAL MADNESS.name: Bestial Madness
BESTIAL MADNESS.flavorText: "Hey this isn't what we were trying to excavate!"

SNOWBALL FIGHT!.name: Snowball Fight!
SNOWBALL FIGHT!.flavorText: Woahwoahwoah, we said no friendly fire!

PARTNER ASSIGNMENT.name: Partner Assignment
PARTNER ASSIGNMENT.flavorText: In every group assignment, someone does all the legwork.

SWINDLE.name: Swindle
SWINDLE.flavorText: You know, it's probably just cheaper to find a place that sells the plushie…

NETHERWIND PORTAL.name: Netherwind Portal
NETHERWIND PORTAL.flavorText: More aromatic than a regular portal.

BOOMKIN.name: Boomkin
BOOMKIN.flavorText: Some Druids consider balance to be a state of harmony between the Natural and the Arcane. Others are more focused on the balance of the opponent’s life total versus their own.

SHADOWCASTER.name: Shadowcaster
SHADOWCASTER.flavorText: I mean, it's not creepy if you ASK before you steal their shadow to make a small replica of them to keep on your shelf.

MANA BURN.name: Mana Burn
MANA BURN.flavorText: One way to ensure that they are not prepared.

KABAL CRYSTAL RUNNER.name: Kabal Crystal Runner
KABAL CRYSTAL RUNNER.flavorText: "Listen, I can cut you in on a little of this premium mana, but you can't tell my boss."

STAR STUDENT STELINA.name: Star Student Stelina
STAR STUDENT STELINA.flavorText: Cheating is just using your resources wisely.

RAS FROSTWHISPER.name: Ras Frostwhisper
RAS FROSTWHISPER.flavorText: Always the favorite of Headmaster Kel'Thuzad, Ras nonetheless received a chilly reception from the other faculty.

RAVASAUR RUNT.name: Ravasaur Runt
RAVASAUR RUNT.flavorText: Doesn't like to adapt unless others are watching. Some minions are such show-offs.

DISARMING ELEMENTAL.name: Disarming Elemental
DISARMING ELEMENTAL.flavorText: "You can have these back when you learn to play nice."

GUARD THE CITY.name: Guard the City
GUARD THE CITY.flavorText: At thousands of feet below the surface, it's a pretty high-pressure job.

MALFURION THE PESTILENT.name: Malfurion the Pestilent
MALFURION THE PESTILENT.flavorText: "Cenarius once taught me about the precarious balance between life and death. I have come to understand: there IS no balance. Death always wins."

KIL'JAEDEN.name: Kil'jaeden
KIL'JAEDEN.flavorText: With complete control of the Burning Legion's forces, Kil'jaeden will stop at nothing until all of the traitorous Draenei have been squelched. *right clicks the enemy hero*

ROWDY FAN.name: Rowdy Fan
ROWDY FAN.flavorText: "This song is so good, it makes me want to PUNCH SOMEONE IN THE FACE!!"

SAFETY EXPERT.name: Safety Expert
SAFETY EXPERT.flavorText: Remember: Always wear your helmet when strapped to a bajillion explosives.

MARIN THE FOX.name: Marin the Fox
MARIN THE FOX.flavorText: My name is Marin the Fox. You took my treasure. Prepare to die.

EVIL MISCREANT.name: EVIL Miscreant
EVIL MISCREANT.flavorText: Because there are no G.O.O.D. Miscreants.

VOLATILE ELEMENTAL.name: Volatile Elemental
VOLATILE ELEMENTAL.flavorText: Currently in an anger management class with Raging Worgen, Grommash Hellscream, and The Angry Chicken. It isn't helping.

RISKY SKIPPER.name: Risky Skipper
RISKY SKIPPER.flavorText: Sworn enemy of the Safety Matey.

TWILIGHT DARKMENDER.name: Twilight Darkmender
TWILIGHT DARKMENDER.flavorText: First she separates them from the lights, washes them in cold water, and hang-dries.

SCALE REPLICA.name: Scale Replica
SCALE REPLICA.flavorText: Get it!?! It's because dragons have hides - commonly known as scales - and this is a model of a dragon on a smaller level, also known as a scale. IT'S THE SAME WORD!

CLEAN THE SCENE.name: Clean the Scene
CLEAN THE SCENE.flavorText: Not even the holy Light can get anima out of white silk.

MARK OF SCORN.name: Mark of Scorn
MARK OF SCORN.flavorText: Threat Level who? Mark of Scorn!

MINOTAUREN.name: Minotauren
MINOTAUREN.flavorText: "Why's he so mad?" "He's been stuck on one of Hearthstone's hidden maze puzzles for YEARS."

SANDSTORM ELEMENTAL.name: Sandstorm Elemental
SANDSTORM ELEMENTAL.flavorText: Doot doot doot doot doot [Pause] Doot doot doot doot doot DEE doot doot doot doot doot!

FOREST WARDEN OMU.name: Forest Warden Omu
FOREST WARDEN OMU.flavorText: She wishes all things could grow and flourish at Scholomance. If only she knew…

ADAPTATION.name: Adaptation
ADAPTATION.flavorText: Pray for salvation. If that fails, pray for extra horns or bigger teeth.

BLOODHOOF BRAVE.name: Bloodhoof Brave
BLOODHOOF BRAVE.flavorText: He thought the set was called "Flippers of the Old Cods" and hungrily volunteered to be in it. He is definitely going to get his hearing checked.

K'URE, THE LIGHT BEYOND.name: K'ure, the Light Beyond
K'URE, THE LIGHT BEYOND.flavorText: The Draenei's story of survival should instill hope in you that anything is possible!! As long as you have the aid of an interdimensional manifestation of holy energy.

INCORPOREAL CORPORAL.name: Incorporeal Corporal
INCORPOREAL CORPORAL.flavorText: You won't believe how long this was called "Incorporal Corporeal"…

GIANT TUMBLEWEED!!!.name: Giant Tumbleweed!!!
GIANT TUMBLEWEED!!!.flavorText: Skarr's second-biggest hobby after laying waste to the Badlands is bowling.

ROKARA.name: Rokara
ROKARA.flavorText: "Tread carefully, but stand tall, and stand together. For strength and honor!" —Rokara

MANAFEEDER PANTHARA.name: Manafeeder Panthara
MANAFEEDER PANTHARA.flavorText: Feeds on mana, crystal kibble, and whatever it was you were just snacking on.

NESTING ROC.name: Nesting Roc
NESTING ROC.flavorText: Roc eggs are great in omelettes, sandwiches, and as bait to turn poachers into bird food.

FROST LICH JAINA.name: Frost Lich Jaina
FROST LICH JAINA.flavorText: "Arthas was a spoiled child, playing with toys he could neither control nor understand. Come into the cold. I will show you the true power of the Frozen Throne."

SPIDER TANK.name: Spider Tank
SPIDER TANK.flavorText: "What if we put guns on it?" -Fizzblitz, staring at the spider-transportation-machine

DEADLY SHOT.name: Deadly Shot
DEADLY SHOT.flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

A. F. KAY.name: A. F. Kay
A. F. KAY.flavorText: Talk to the hand 'cause the mouth is sippin'.

ILLIDAN STORMRAGE.name: Illidan Stormrage
ILLIDAN STORMRAGE.flavorText: Illidan's brother, Malfurion, imprisoned him beneath Hyjal for 10,000 years. Stormrages are not good at letting go of grudges.
